HEADWORD: Nix
<hw>Nix</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <pos>fem.</pos> <er>Nixe</er>
<pr>(<?/)</pr>. <ety>[G. Cf. 1st <er>Nick</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Teut.
Myth.)</fld> <def>One of a class of water spirits, commonly described as
of a mischievous disposition.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The treacherous <qex>nixes</qex> who entice men to a watery
death.</q> <rj><qau>Tylor.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nixie</ent>⟦br⟧
